
How to call the executable:

./AS_ConfigurableSystem bkg sfgd classif pdetect source_video_path short_name FOLDER_results_path (mask_path)

(mask path only if required)

Example (without mask):

./AS_ConfigurableSystem 2 1 1 1 ../Datasets/VISOR/visor_Video00.avi visor_Video00 ../Results/Category_easy/

******************************************************************************************



Files/Folder structure:

-> Datasets
        -> VISOR
                - Video file
                - GT (.txt)
        -> ...
        -> ...

-> bin
        -> AS_ConfigurableSystem (executable)
        -> viper files
        -> lib (viper libraries)


-> Results
        -> Category_easy
        -> Category_medium
        -> Category_hard


-> Images
        -> Mask for AVSS videos


-> Category_easy.txt (contains paths of videos belonging to this categgory)
-> Category_medium.txt
-> Category_hard.txt

-> Execute_AS_ConfigurableSystem.sh (Executable)
-> eval_viper_AS_ConfigurableSystem.sh (file calling viper-pe) THIS SCRIPT SHOULD BE IN SAME PATH THAN VIPER FILES AND VIPER LIB FOLDER.. (bin)

-> Extract_Results.m (Matlab file for post-processing the results)
-> Compute_scores.m (Matlab file for post-processing the results)







